[
  {"league":"MLB","leagueName":"Major League Baseball","country":"USA, Canada","colorCode":"#161F30","foundedYear":"1903\nNational League: 1876\nAmerican League: 1901\nMerged into one organization: 2000","numberOfTeams":"30","leagueNames":"American League, National League","divisionNames":"West, Central, East","mostTitles":"New York Yankees - (27 Titles)","mostRecentTitles":"Los Angeles Dodgers","website":"www.mlb.com","logoFileName":"ball_logo_mlb.png","description":"Major League Baseball is the highest level of professional baseball in the world, featuring teams across the United States and Canada. Founded in 1903 through the partnership of the American League and National League, MLB represents the pinnacle of the sport, showcasing the best players, historic franchises, and iconic ballparks. Each season culminates in the World Series, where the champions of the two leagues compete for baseball’s ultimate title. With more than a century of history, MLB remains one of the most influential and tradition-rich sports leagues globally."},
  {"league":"IL","leagueName":"International League","country":"USA","colorCode":"#111B37","foundedYear":"1884","numberOfTeams":"20","divisionNames":"East, West","mostTitles":"Rochester Red Wings - (19 Titles)","mostRecentTitles":"Jacksonville Jumbo Shrimp","website":"wwww.milb.com","logoFileName":"ball_logo_il.png","description":"The International League is a Triple-A Minor League Baseball league and one of the primary development leagues for Major League Baseball teams. It is one of the oldest professional baseball leagues in the world. The league features top prospects and experienced players who are one step away from the major leagues. Teams are located across the eastern and midwestern United States, serving as key affiliates for MLB organizations and providing fans with high-level professional baseball."},
  {"league":"PCL","leagueName":"Pacific Coast League","country":"USA","colorCode":"#8FB4E0","foundedYear":"1903","numberOfTeams":"10","divisionNames":"East, West","mostTitles":"Sacramento Solons - (14 Titles)","mostRecentTitles":"Oklahoma City Baseball Club","website":"www.milb.com","logoFileName":"ball_logo_pcl.png","description":"The Pacific Coast League is a Triple-A Minor League Baseball league and one of the highest levels of professional baseball below Major League Baseball. Founded in 1903, the league has a long history of developing top prospects and experienced players preparing for the major leagues. Teams are located primarily across the western and central United States and serve as key affiliates for MLB organizations, providing fans with high-level professional baseball and a final step in the path to the majors."},
  {"league":"EL","leagueName":"Eastern League","country":"USA","colorCode":"#08193B","foundedYear":"1923","numberOfTeams":"12","divisionNames":"Northeast, Southeast","mostTitles":"Binghamton Triplets - (10 Titles)","mostRecentTitles":"Binghampton Rumble Ponies","website":"www.milb.com","logoFileName":"ball_logo_el.png","description":"The Eastern League is one of the three Double-A leagues in Minor League Baseball and sits one level below Triple-A, which means it is usually the last major development stop before Major League Baseball. It is widely viewed as the level where prospects first face pitchers and hitters with genuine major league projection."},
